## Implementation Overview

### 1. LiveLogger SSE Integration
- Modify the existing LiveLogger class to automatically emit SSE messages for every log event
- Create a new `SSELogEmitter` class that:
  ```typescript
  class SSELogEmitter {
    private sseConnections: Map<string, Response>;

    emit(logEntry: LogEntry) {
      const sseMessage = this.formatSSEMessage(logEntry);
      this.broadcast(sseMessage);
    }

    private formatSSEMessage(entry: LogEntry): string {
      return `event: log\ndata: ${JSON.stringify({
        timestamp: entry.timestamp,
        level: entry.level,
        message: entry.message,
        correlationId: entry.correlationId,
        metadata: entry.metadata
      })}\n\n`;
    }
  }
  ```

### 2. Correlation ID Implementation
- Generate unique correlation IDs using UUID v4 for each request/operation
- Implement correlation ID propagation:
  ```typescript
  interface CorrelationContext {
    correlationId: string;
    parentId?: string;
    spanId: string;
    service: string;
  }

  class CorrelationManager {
    static createContext(parentId?: string): CorrelationContext {
      return {
        correlationId: parentId || uuidv4(),
        parentId,
        spanId: uuidv4(),
        service: process.env.SERVICE_NAME || 'cv2web'
      };
    }
  }
  ```
- Add correlation ID to all log entries automatically
- Pass correlation IDs through HTTP headers for cross-service communication

### 3. Performance Metrics Collection
- Implement performance tracking decorators:
  ```typescript
  @measurePerformance()
  async processCV(data: CVData): Promise<Result> {
    // Method implementation
  }
  ```
- Track key metrics:
  - Method execution time
  - Memory usage snapshots
  - CPU utilization
  - Request/response sizes
  - Database query times
- Emit performance data through SSE:
  ```typescript
  event: metrics
  data: {
    "correlationId": "abc-123",
    "operation": "cv.extraction",
    "duration": 1234,
    "memory": { "used": 256, "total": 512 },
    "timestamp": "2024-01-01T12:00:00Z"
  }
  ```

### 4. Log Aggregation System
- Create centralized log storage using a time-series approach
- Implement log buffering to batch writes for performance:
  ```typescript
  class LogAggregator {
    private buffer: LogEntry[] = [];
    private flushInterval = 5000; // 5 seconds

    async aggregate(entry: LogEntry) {
      this.buffer.push(entry);
      if (this.buffer.length >= 100) {
        await this.flush();
      }
    }

    private async flush() {
      // Batch insert to database
      await db.logs.insertMany(this.buffer);
      this.buffer = [];
    }
  }
  ```
- Create indexes on correlation ID, timestamp, and log level for efficient querying
- Implement log retention policies (e.g., keep detailed logs for 7 days, aggregated logs for 30 days)

### 5. Enhanced LiveLogger API
- Extend LiveLogger with new methods:
  ```typescript
  class LiveLogger {
    constructor(
      private sseEmitter: SSELogEmitter,
      private aggregator: LogAggregator,
      private metricsCollector: MetricsCollector
    ) {}

    async log(level: LogLevel, message: string, metadata?: any) {
      const entry = this.createLogEntry(level, message, metadata);

      // Emit via SSE
      this.sseEmitter.emit(entry);

      // Store in aggregation system
      await this.aggregator.aggregate(entry);

      // Collect metrics if applicable
      if (metadata?.metrics) {
        this.metricsCollector.record(metadata.metrics);
      }
    }

    withCorrelation(correlationId: string): LiveLogger {
      // Return a logger instance bound to specific correlation ID
    }
  }
  ```

### 6. SSE Message Types for Logging
Define standardized log event types:
- `log:info` - Informational messages
- `log:warning` - Warning messages
- `log:error` - Error messages with stack traces
- `log:debug` - Debug information (only in development)
- `metrics` - Performance metrics
- `correlation:start` - Beginning of correlated operation
- `correlation:end` - End of correlated operation

## Implementation Overview

### 1. Claude Code SDK Setup and Configuration
- Install and configure @anthropic-ai/claude-code SDK:
  ```typescript
  npm install @anthropic-ai/claude-code
  ```
- Create Claude client with advanced configuration:
  ```typescript
  import { ClaudeCode } from '@anthropic-ai/claude-code';

  const claudeClient = new ClaudeCode({
    apiKey: process.env.CLAUDE_API_KEY,
    maxRetries: 3,
    retryDelay: 1000,
    timeout: 30000,
    streaming: true,
    caching: {
      enabled: true,
      ttl: 3600, // 1 hour cache
      maxSize: 100 // Max cached responses
    }
  });
  ```

### 2. Implement Retry Logic with Exponential Backoff
- Create retry wrapper for Claude API calls:
  ```typescript
  class ClaudeRetryHandler {
    async executeWithRetry<T>(
      operation: () => Promise<T>,
      maxRetries: number = 3
    ): Promise<T> {
      let lastError: Error;

      for (let attempt = 0; attempt < maxRetries; attempt++) {
        try {
          return await operation();
        } catch (error) {
          lastError = error;
          const delay = Math.min(1000 * Math.pow(2, attempt), 10000);
          await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, delay));
        }
      }

      throw new Error(`Failed after ${maxRetries} attempts: ${lastError.message}`);
    }
  }
  ```

### 3. Set Up Response Caching Layer
- Implement intelligent caching for Claude responses:
  ```typescript
  class ClaudeResponseCache {
    private cache: Map<string, CachedResponse>;

    generateCacheKey(prompt: string, params: object): string {
      return crypto.createHash('sha256')
        .update(JSON.stringify({ prompt, params }))
        .digest('hex');
    }

    async get(key: string): Promise<CachedResponse | null> {
      const cached = this.cache.get(key);
      if (cached && cached.expiresAt > Date.now()) {
        return cached;
      }
      return null;
    }

    set(key: string, response: any, ttl: number): void {
      this.cache.set(key, {
        response,
        expiresAt: Date.now() + ttl * 1000,
        createdAt: Date.now()
      });
    }
  }
  ```

### 4. Configure Tool Permissions and Capabilities
- Define Claude tool permissions for portfolio generation:
  ```typescript
  const claudeTools = {
    codeGeneration: {
      enabled: true,
      languages: ['typescript', 'javascript', 'html', 'css'],
      maxFileSize: 50000,
      allowedOperations: ['create', 'modify', 'analyze']
    },
    webSearch: {
      enabled: false // Disabled for security
    },
    fileSystem: {
      enabled: true,
      sandboxed: true,
      allowedPaths: ['/tmp/portfolio-generation']
    }
  };
  ```

### 5. Implement Streaming Response Handler
- Create SSE-compatible streaming handler for Claude responses:
  ```typescript
  class ClaudeStreamHandler {
    async streamPortfolioGeneration(
      prompt: string,
      sseEmitter: SSEEmitter
    ): Promise<void> {
      const stream = await claudeClient.createStream({
        model: 'claude-3-opus-20240229',
        messages: [{ role: 'user', content: prompt }],
        stream: true,
        max_tokens: 4000
      });

      for await (const chunk of stream) {
        if (chunk.type === 'content_block_delta') {
          sseEmitter.emit({
            type: 'claude_generation',
            data: {
              content: chunk.delta.text,
              isPartial: true
            }
          });
        }
      }
    }
  }
  ```

### 6. Create Hybrid AI Generation Service
- Implement service combining Gemini CV extraction with Claude portfolio generation:
  ```typescript
  class HybridAIPortfolioService {
    constructor(
      private geminiExtractor: GeminiCVExtractor,
      private claudeGenerator: ClaudePortfolioGenerator,
      private liveLogger: LiveLogger
    ) {}

    async generatePortfolio(cvFile: File): Promise<Portfolio> {
      // Step 1: Extract CV data using Gemini
      this.liveLogger.info('Starting CV extraction with Gemini', {
        correlationId: generateCorrelationId(),
        service: 'hybrid-ai'
      });

      const cvData = await this.geminiExtractor.extract(cvFile);

      // Step 2: Generate creative components with Claude
      this.liveLogger.info('Generating portfolio with Claude', {
        extractedSections: Object.keys(cvData)
      });

      const portfolioPrompt = this.buildPortfolioPrompt(cvData);
      const portfolio = await this.claudeGenerator.generate(portfolioPrompt);

      return this.mergeResults(cvData, portfolio);
    }

    private buildPortfolioPrompt(cvData: CVData): string {
      return `Generate a creative portfolio website based on the following CV data:

        Professional Summary: ${cvData.summary}
        Skills: ${cvData.skills.join(', ')}
        Experience: ${JSON.stringify(cvData.experience)}

        Requirements:
        - Modern, responsive design
        - Interactive components
        - Smooth animations
        - Professional color scheme
        - SEO optimized structure`;
    }
  }
  ```

### 7. Implement Error Handling and Fallback Strategies
- Create comprehensive error handling:
  ```typescript
  class ClaudeErrorHandler {
    handleError(error: ClaudeError): ErrorResponse {
      switch (error.type) {
        case 'rate_limit':
          return {
            message: 'Rate limit exceeded',
            retryAfter: error.retryAfter,
            fallbackStrategy: 'use_cached_response'
          };
        case 'invalid_request':
          return {
            message: 'Invalid request parameters',
            details: error.details,
            fallbackStrategy: 'simplify_prompt'
          };
        case 'timeout':
          return {
            message: 'Request timeout',
            fallbackStrategy: 'retry_with_shorter_prompt'
          };
        default:
          return {
            message: 'Unknown error',
            fallbackStrategy: 'use_gemini_fallback'
          };
      }
    }
  }
  ```

### 8. Create Configuration Management
- Implement dynamic configuration for Claude parameters:
  ```typescript
  interface ClaudeConfig {
    model: string;
    temperature: number;
    maxTokens: number;
    topP: number;
    frequencyPenalty: number;
    presencePenalty: number;
  }

  class ClaudeConfigManager {
    private configs: Map<string, ClaudeConfig> = new Map([
      ['creative', {
        model: 'claude-3-opus-20240229',
        temperature: 0.8,
        maxTokens: 4000,
        topP: 0.9,
        frequencyPenalty: 0.3,
        presencePenalty: 0.3
      }],
      ['technical', {
        model: 'claude-3-sonnet-20240229',
        temperature: 0.3,
        maxTokens: 3000,
        topP: 0.95,
        frequencyPenalty: 0.1,
        presencePenalty: 0.1
      }]
    ]);

    getConfig(type: string): ClaudeConfig {
      return this.configs.get(type) || this.configs.get('creative');
    }
  }
  ```

